<br>
Now, that said, I hear it alot.  It's disturbing, but I do not think alot of people mean anything by it...by using it you become desensitized to it, and it becomes just another word.  Enter the military and you will become so desensitized to curse words that when someone shouts at you without using them you'll actually feel worse than if they had!<br>
<br>
Now that I've defended the ignorant, I have to play Devil's Advocate to myself.  I really hate that this is going around like it is.  I've heard it alot...for a long time honestly...in EQ.  In FPS games it's thrown around commonly.  But I hear people come here, complain that keys aren't no drop or that they can't bind anywhere they want, and immediately That's Gay.  Someone was using the shout channel in GFay as their own little talk show or something, complaining about Arboreans don't drop amber or bark enough, and I heard the term enough that for the first time ever I've turned off the shout channel.<br>
<br>
It's really a nasty thing, and I hope that in the years to come we'll look down on it as hard as most of us look down on racial slurs.  Noone's race or sexuality should be an object of insult, especially over a silly game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/1/02 4:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That is so str8!</span><hr size=1> Not everyone who says a phrase bothers to think through it's origins.<br>
